args: According to this data...it is\nimpossible to give my heart to Finni.
No... How can I fix her heart, then?
Emergency repairs have stabilized her\nfor the time being, but her heart has to\nbe approaching its limit.
She's only one injury away from going\nberserk...or worse.
She could completely lose her heart.\nHer very consciousness might disappear!
I can't even fathom the idea of her\nbeing gone. She's been by my side\nfor a thousand years now.
No. No, no, no.\nI will NOT let that come to pass!
What?! I'm surrounded! I can't believe\nI didn't notice them approaching...
I must have devoted too many resources\nto analyzing the blueprint.
Command from Anassa accepted.\nTerminating defector unit Eirene.
So many enemies... It's going to be\ndifficult to force my way through their\nranks.
This bodes ill. The longer this drags on,\nthe more I risk being caught between the\nunits here now and their reinforcements.
Wait... I'm picking up more enemy\nsignatures to the rear. They DID\nmanage to catch up to me!
I'm completely surrounded. This is the\nworst-case scenario. Can I even return\nto the Halidom safely at this point?
Forgive me, Finni. Here I was worrying\nabout your heart breaking down, but it\nlooks like I might stop functioning first...
Finni! Yes—for now, I am!\nBut what are you doing here?!
Square up, you bastards. You'll pay\nfor trying to hurt Eirene. Prepare to\nbe decommissioned! HRAAAGH!
Ha-HA! How'd you like that little\nbit of tag-team action, punks?
You're a lifesaver, Finni.\nBut why are you here?
Laxi filled me in on where you went.

I know you're a great strategist and all,
but I couldn't help but worry. My fears
were confirmed once I saw a huge fuss
around the base, and...well, here I am.
I see. I'm sorry for worrying you.
I managed to accomplish my objective,\nbut Anassa discovered my identity.
No, Eirene. That's not what I want you\nto apologize for.
Why were you even thinking of giving me\nyour own heart?
Because...I wanted to fix yours, and—
But if you did that, wouldn't you end\nup like Mascula and stop functioning?!
I don't wanna live in a world built\non the back of your sacrifice!
I could never deal with losing the person\nwho's been by my side for a millennium!
(You don't want to lose me in the\nsame way I don't want to lose you.)
I'm sorry... I didn't even consider how\nmuch it would hurt you to be left behind\nif I were to stop functioning.
As long as you understand now.\nBut let this be the end of you trying\nto sacrifice yourself for me, okay?
If either one of us leaves the other, the one\nwho remains will be lonely. When we do\nstop functioning, we'll do it together!
Yes. I promise, Finni. When we\ncease to function, it will be as one.
Finni?! Your heart... No, it can't be! Did\nthe fight with those androids damage it?!
Agh! Stop, Finni!\nDon't you recognize me?!
Oh no... Has her heart malfunctioned\nentirely? Has she lost all control?
No...this can't be...\nPlease, go back to normal!\nFinni... Finni!
